# Schema Version Registry
#
# Single source of truth for "what's the current version of every Loom schema".
# Read by /loom-upgrade detection logic, the install-state writer, and tests.
#
# This registry is HUMAN-AUTHORITATIVE. Code mirrors `currentVersion` in
# module-level `CURRENT_VERSION` constants (one per "module" kind migrator).
# The parity test in `test/protocol/schema-upgrade-v3.test.ts` guards against
# drift: if you bump currentVersion here but forget to bump CURRENT_VERSION in
# the migrator, the test fails. The reverse — bumping the constant without
# bumping the registry — also fails because the test reads this file by name.
#
# Adding a new schema version: see "Adding a New Schema Version" in
# schema-upgrade.md.

schemaVersion: 1
lastUpdated: 2026-06-04

# `migratorKind` values:
#   - "module"   → typed migrator module exporting MIGRATIONS + migrateToLatest()
#   - "inline"   → migration logic lives directly in /loom-upgrade (Rule N steps)
#   - "agent"    → structural migration via an upgrade agent (Tier C)
#   - "scaffold" → empty structure created when missing (no version concept)
#   - "static"   → no migration ever; file is read at current version or not at all
#
# `pathKind` values:
#   - "home"     → home-relative (~/.claude/…)
#   - "literal"  → literal path relative to project root
#   - "glob"     → glob pattern (e.g. *.agent-result.toon)
#   - "dir"      → directory containing many files of this schema kind
#
# `migratorPath` values:
#   - "module" kind  → relative path to the TS migrator module
#   - "inline" kind  → rule anchor in schema-upgrade.md (e.g. schema-upgrade.md#rule-1)
#   - "agent" kind   → path to the upgrade agent .md file
#   - "scaffold"/"static" kinds → "—" (no executable migrator)

registry[19]{schema,file,pathKind,currentVersion,migratorKind,migratorPath,rule}:
  install-state,~/.claude/skills/library/install-state.toon,home,3,module,hooks/lib/install-state-migrator.ts,12
  library-catalog,~/.claude/skills/library/library.yaml,home,3,module,hooks/lib/library-catalog-migrator.ts,13
  criteria-plan,*/criteria-plan.toon,glob,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-1,1
  agent-result,*.agent-result.toon,glob,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-2,2
  plan,PLAN.md,literal,2,agent,agents/plan-upgrade-agent.md,3
  state,.plan-execution/state.toon,literal,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-4,4
  convergence-tier,convergence-tier.schema.md,literal,1,static,—,5
  orchestration-config,.claude/orchestration.toml,literal,2,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-6,6
  roadmap,ROADMAP.md,literal,1,agent,agents/roadmap-upgrade-agent.md,7
  claude-md,CLAUDE.md,literal,2,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-8,8
  hooks,.claude/settings.json,literal,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-9,9
  wiki-index,.loom/wiki/index.toon,literal,1,scaffold,—,10
  protocols,agents/protocols/,dir,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-11,11
  scope-contract,*/scope-contract.toon,glob,1,static,—,—
  scenario,*/scenarios/,dir,1,static,—,—
  change-proposal,.loom/changes/*/proposal.md,glob,1,static,—,—
  change-state,.loom/changes/*/state.toon,glob,1,static,—,—
  contract-page-extensions,.loom/wiki/pages/contract-*.md,glob,1,static,—,—
  plan-artifact-layout,ROADMAP.md|PLAN*.md|.plan-history/,literal,1,inline,schema-upgrade.md#rule-14,14

# When a schema's currentVersion bumps:
#   1. Update currentVersion above.
#   2. Update the migratorKind if changing (e.g., "static" → "module").
#   3. For "module" kind: add migrateVNToVN+1 to the migrator's MIGRATIONS map.
#      Bump the exported `CURRENT_VERSION` constant in the migrator to match.
#   4. For "inline" kind: extend the rule body in schema-upgrade.md.
#   5. Add a fixture pair under test-fixtures/<schema>-migration/.
#   6. If your new step needs options the prior step didn't, extend
#      MigrationOptions with OPTIONAL fields only. Required-option changes
#      break backward compat for chain walks; reserve those for v(N+1) bumps
#      where every step is being rewritten.
